- The specific pricing strategy (id = 2) is assumed for simplicity, indicating a particular method of calculating prices for energy products;
- Forecasted prices and mean prices are used to estimate future energy costs;
- Energy consumption forecasting is based on historical data and seasonal factors.

sql:
SELECT AVG(net_margin) AS avg_net_margin, MAX(pow_max) AS max_pow_max
FROM customer_analysis
WHERE churn = 1 AND year = 2022;

SELECT product_name
FROM energy_products
WHERE unit_price > 0.15;

SELECT client_id, net_margin
FROM customer_analysis
ORDER BY net_margin DESC;

